    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-09-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                <head>No. 224.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-09-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 2,
                                    1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 115.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatches numbered <pb facs="0386" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/> 143 and
                            146, with reference to the case of Mr. Charles F. Teel, to which the
                            latter relates. I have to inform you that the Department will await a
                            further report from you.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
